    <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="can-i-hire-someone-to-add-experience-signals-to-my">
      <span class="faq-q-text">Can I hire someone to add experience signals to my AI content?</span>
      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="can-i-hire-someone-to-add-experience-signals-to-my"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes, but with a caveat. The person adding experience signals needs to have the actual experience. A general editor cannot inject real first-hand knowledge they do not possess. What they can do is interview someone with experience, extract specific details, and weave those into the content. This interview-based approach is common in journalism and works well for content operations. The key is that the experience must come from a real source, not be invented by the writer.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
